    ],
    "summary": "On 29 March 2019 at 19:25 hours, while conducting abandonment operations of Tubular Bells Well TB001 sidetrack aboard the Diamond Ocean BlackLion drillship, a 7 x 5-1/2 inch tubing string was dropped into the well after the hydraulic elevators opened prematurely while supporting approximately 170,000 lbs of string weight. The tubing string fell through the slips and three control line flat packs were lost downhole. No injuries or environmental impacts occurred.",
    "recommendations": [
      "Incorporate a safety device to restrict opening the elevator or the slips when supporting tubular",
      "Install a pipe clamp when pulling external flush connection tubular",
      "Consider issuance of a Safety Alert"
    ],
